<TITLE> One killed, 12 injured as Puja revellers clash in old Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 29 (bdnews24.com)Clashes between two rival groups of Puja revellers at Sutrapur in the city Monday night left one killed and at least 12 persons injured, police said. The dead, Goutam Sarkar, 24, was the president of Swechchhasevak League of ward 79. The wounded were treated at local hospitals. Sutrapur police chief Tofazzal Hossain told bdnews24.com that there had been prior rivalries over influence and authority between the organizers of two local Puja pavalions. At one stage, the two sides engaged in hitting each other which took a serious turn as the two camps used bombs and guns. Police had to fire blank shots to stop the fighting. Goutam got killed later in the aftermath of the conflicts, Hossain said. An eye witness said that at midnight when the Bhushir Goli Durga idol was being taken around before immersion, its carriers engaged in a brawl and fisticuffs with the volunteers of Panchbarhi Puja pavilion. Later, as the Bhushir Goli processionists arrived in front of Lal Kuthi, two shots were fired at them. Goutam was badly hit and Pankaj Sarkar was injured in his hand and leg. Goutam, son of Dhirendra Sarkar, was a fruit trader at Shyam Bazar. b
